data.title: Startup challenge showcases Mumbai as global innovation hub
data.meta_description: The StartUp Mumbai Challenge, held as part of the Mumbai Festival, showcased Mumbai as a global innovation hub. The challenge focused on eco-friendly living and sustainability, with ten startups and entrepreneurs presenting their ideas. The event was supported by Turbostart and United Nations India, aligning with PM Narendra Modi's Mission LiFE and India's commitment to the UN Sustainable Development Goals. The challenge emphasized Mumbai's identity as a global innovation center and received government support from Maharashtra's deputy chief minister. The panel discussion highlighted the importance of breaking barriers and building sustainability for startups.
